# Forge Developer Guide — {{ model.names.dot_net_class_name }}

> Generated by Pervaxis Forge for the **{{ model.manifest.product }}** vertical.
> This guide is your primary reference for writing vertical domain code on this service.

---

## 1. The Contract: What You Own vs What You Don't

### You own (vertical code)
- `Services/` — service implementation and domain logic
- `Data/` — EF Core `DbContext`, entities, repositories, migrations
- `Models/` — request/response records and domain models
- `Controllers/` — endpoint logic, routing, validation
- `Tests/` — all test cases

### You do NOT touch (horizontal — raise a Pervaxis ticket for changes)
- `Program.cs` — app startup and Genesis module wiring
- `Extensions/ServiceCollectionExtensions.cs` — DI registration structure
- `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.*` — container configuration
- `.github/workflows/` — CI/CD pipelines
- `.claude/guides/`, `.claude/skills/` — platform standards
- `appsettings.json` — configuration schema

If you find yourself editing a horizontal file, stop and raise a Pervaxis platform ticket.

---

## 2. Architecture

```
HTTP Request
    │
    ▼
{{ model.names.dot_net_class_name }}Controller     ← You write: routing, validation, error mapping
    │
    ▼
I{{ model.names.dot_net_class_name }}              ← You write: business logic, orchestration
    │
    ├──► IYourDomainRepository                     ← You write: data access via EF Core
    │        │
    │        ▼
    │    YourDomainDbContext                        ← You write: entities, migrations
    │
{{ for module in model.selected_modules }}    └──► {{ module.package_name }}
{{ end }}
```

**Layer rules:**
- Controllers handle HTTP concerns only — no business logic, no EF Core
- Services handle domain logic — no HTTP context, no direct EF Core
- Repositories handle data access only — no domain rules
- Genesis providers are called from the service layer only

