## 8. Observability

Every service method must be instrumented. Ship no dark code. See `.claude/guides/OBSERVABILITY_PATTERN.md` for the full pattern.

### Logging

```csharp
// Normal operations
_logger.LogInformation("Fetching record {RecordId}", id);

// Expected failures
_logger.LogWarning("Record {RecordId} not found", id);

// Unexpected failures
_logger.LogError(ex, "Failed to create record with reference {Reference}", request.Reference);
```

**Rules:** Never log PII. Always use structured properties — never string interpolation in log messages.

### Tracing

```csharp
private static readonly ActivitySource ActivitySource = new("{{ model.names.namespace }}");

using var activity = ActivitySource.StartActivity("{{ model.manifest.service_name }}.get");
activity?.SetTag("record.id", id);
activity?.SetStatus(ActivityStatusCode.Ok);
```

### Metrics

```csharp
private static readonly Meter Meter = new("{{ model.names.namespace }}");
private static readonly Counter<long> OperationsCounter =
    Meter.CreateCounter<long>("{{ model.manifest.service_name }}.operations");

OperationsCounter.Add(1, new TagList { { "operation", "get" }, { "result", "success" } });
```

